import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['speed'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Driving Speeds')
    plt.axvline(data['speed'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['speed'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Speed (mph)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of driving speeds?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['driving_speed'], data['fuel_efficiency'])
    plt.xlabel('Driving Speed')
    plt.ylabel('Fuel Efficiency')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between driving speed and fuel efficiency?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = data['distance'].astype(float)
    plt.hist(data['distance'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Distances')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['distance'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Distance Traveled per Trip')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of distances traveled per trip?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['trip_duration'] = pd.to_numeric(data['trip_duration'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['trip_duration'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['trip_duration'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Trip Durations')
    plt.axvline(data['trip_duration'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['trip_duration'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Trip Duration')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of trip durations?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['trip_duration'], data['distance_traveled'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Trip Duration')
    ax.set_ylabel('Distance Traveled')
    ax.set_title('Is there a correlation between trip duration and distance traveled?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
